					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yeah, detecting HBlank isn't a real problem.
<br />The real problem is :
<br />bit $2002
<br />bvc -
<br />
<br />Takes 4 + 3 CPU cycles, so 7 CPU cycles in total. That means the hit can wrap arround 7*3=21 pixels. So in the best case you can time it to be just in HBlank and 21 pixels later in the worst case, but then if leaves you few time to be sure that your PPU writes will end before the begining of the next scanline in the worst case.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

