					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">That basically works.  But don't put it on the rightmost 8 pixels, it doesn't detect a hit there (just another PPU quirk, I think my 'RTC' demo locks up because of that).
<br />
<br />But there are timing issues, like blargg was showing.  You can't detect a hit at  the exact same time every frame.  The margin of error needs to fit within hblank.
<br />
<br />It's not a good replacement for IRQs though.  Considering that you only get one sprite 0 hit per frame, and also the program has to waste time polling.  Sprite 0 is fine though if you just want one hit really early or late in the frame.</div>

